s($,"bc7","aS8",()=>A.Pu("Filtering, column creation, and basic aggregation.",A.b([A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"',"Find all ERROR-level logs from your microservices application.","Application Logs","The filter verb is the most fundamental OPAL verb. Place filters as early as possible in your pipeline to reduce the data volume for subsequent operations.","Example 1: Filtering Logs by Severity"),A.fP('make_col\n  response_time_ms: float64(response_time_ns) / 1000000.0,\n  is_error: status_code >= 400,\n  endpoint: concat(method, " ", path)\npick_col timestamp, endpoint, status_code, response_time_ms, is_error',"Enrich HTTP access log data with a human-readable response time and an error flag.","HTTP Access Logs","make_col creates new columns (or overwrites existing ones). pick_col selects only the columns you want, dropping everything else. Together they are the most common projection operations.","Example 2: Creating Computed Columns"),A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"\nstatsby error_count:count(1), group_by(service)\nsort desc(error_count)',"Count the total number of errors per service over the last hour to identify which services are most problematic.","Application Logs (query window: last 1 hour)","The checkout service has ~3x more errors than the next service. This warrants immediate investigation.","Example 3: Basic Aggregation \u2014 Error Count by Service")],t.LK),"IC1","IC1 \u2014 Basics"))
s($,"bc8","aS9",()=>A.Pu("Time-series aggregations and top-K analysis.",A.b([A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"\ntimechart 5m, error_count:count(1), group_by(service)',"Visualize error rates over time, broken down by service, using 5-minute buckets.","Application Logs (query window: last 6 hours)","timechart produces streamable output (can be accelerated into a Dataset), while statsby is unstreamable (useful only in Worksheets for ad-hoc queries).","Example 4: Time-Series Aggregation with timechart"),A.fP('make_col endpoint: concat(method, " ", path)\ntopk 5, count:count(1), group_by(endpoint)',"Find the top 5 endpoints by request count.","HTTP Access Logs","topk is a convenient shorthand for aggregation + sort + limit. It returns the top N groups by a given metric.","Example 5: Top-K Analysis")],t.LK),"IC2","IC2 \u2014 Time Series"))
s($,"bc9","aSa",()=>A.Pu("JSON parsing, joins, and regular expressions.",A.b([A.fP('make_col parsed:parse_json(string(FIELDS))\nmake_col\n  service:string(parsed.service),\n  event_type:string(parsed.event.type),\n  event_status:string(parsed.event.status),\n  error_code:int64(parsed.event.error.code),\n  error_message:string(parsed.event.error.message),\n  user_id:string(parsed.user.id),\n  user_tier:string(parsed.user.tier)\nfilter event_status = "failed"\npick_col timestamp, service, event_type, error_code, error_message, user_id, user_tier',"Raw application events arrive with a JSON body. Parse the JSON and extract meaningful fields.","Datastream/Raw Events","JSON parsing is one of the most common operations in Observe. The parse_json() function converts a string column into a structured object you can navigate with dot notation.","Example 6: Parsing JSON and Extracting Nested Fields"),A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"\nleftjoin pod_name = @"Kubernetes/Pod".name,\n  namespace:@"Kubernetes/Pod".namespace,\n  node_name:@"Kubernetes/Pod".node_name,\n  pod_status:@"Kubernetes/Pod".status,\n  restart_count:@"Kubernetes/Pod".restart_count\npick_col timestamp, service, message, pod_name, namespace, node_name, pod_status, restart_count',"Enrich application error logs with Kubernetes pod metadata to understand which nodes and namespaces are affected.","Application Logs + Kubernetes/Pod (resource dataset)","The leftjoin against a resource dataset is temporal \u2014 Observe automatically resolves which version of the pod resource was active at the time of each log event.","Example 7: Enriching Logs via leftjoin"),A.fP('extract_regex message, \n  /\\"(?P<method>GET|POST|PUT|DELETE|PATCH)\\s+(?P<path>\\/\\S+)\\s+HTTP\\/\\S+\\"\\s+(?P<status>\\d{3})\\s+(?P<bytes>\\d+)/\nmake_col\n  status_code:int64(status),\n  bytes_sent:int64(bytes),\n  status_class:concat(substring(status, 1, 1), "xx")\nfilter status_code >= 400\nstatsby \n  error_count:count(1),\n  avg_bytes:avg(bytes_sent),\n  group_by(method, path, status_class)\nsort desc(error_count)',"Parse structured data from unstructured Nginx access log messages and analyze response patterns.","Nginx Access Logs","extract_regex uses named capture groups (?P<name>) to create new columns directly from regex matches. This is extremely powerful for parsing unstructured log formats.","Example 8: Regular Expressions \u2014 Extract and Analyze")],t.LK),"IC3","IC3 \u2014 Intermediate"))
s($,"bca","aSb",()=>A.Pu("Time comparisons, subqueries, and dynamic thresholds.",A.b([A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"\ntimechart 1h, error_count:count(1)\ntimewrap 1w',"Compare this week's error rate against last week to identify anomalies.","Application Logs (query window: last 2 weeks)","timewrap is essential for week-over-week or day-over-day comparisons. Rendered as overlapping line charts, anomalous spikes become immediately visible.","Example 9: Time-Series Comparison with timewrap"),A.fP('filter severity = "ERROR"\ntimechart 1h, error_count:count(1), group_by(service)\n\nfilter error_count > 2 * (\n  @"Application Logs"\n  | filter severity = "ERROR"\n  | timechart 1h, baseline:count(1), group_by(service)\n  | timeshift 7d\n  | statsby avg_baseline:avg(baseline), group_by(service)\n).avg_baseline',"Find services whose error rate exceeds 2x their 7-day average.","Application Logs","Subqueries allow you to compute dynamic thresholds inline. Here the baseline is the 7-day average error rate per service, and we alert when current exceeds 2x that baseline.","Example 10: Subqueries for Dynamic Thresholds")],t.LK),"IC4","IC4 \u2014 Advanced Time"))
